Language name: YORUBA
Language number: 4137
Alternate names: 
Classification: Niger-Kordofanian, Kwa
Comments: Yoruba has three level tones.  A limited vowel 
harmony system operates, banning co-occurrence of 
higher-mid with lower-mid vowels.  /n/ can be treated in 
most cases as the allophone of /l/ before a nasalized 
vowel.

Sources: 

Bamgbose, A. 1966. A grammar of Yoruba.  Cambridge 
University Press, Cambridge.